Name: selective IgM deficiency disease
Definition: A selective immunoglobulin deficiency disease thatis a dysgammaglobulinemia resulting from decreased levels of immunoglobulin M (IgM) production to roduction of other antibodies.

Name: obsolete candidal gastritis
Definition: A candidiasis that involves inflammation of the gastric mucosa caused by Candida albicans infection. The symptoms include dyspepsia

Name: obsolete Helicobacter heilmannii infectious disease
Definition: A primary Helicobacter infectious disease that involves inflammation of the stomach lining caused by Candidatus Helicobacter heilmannii

Name: obsolete Histoplasma capsulatum gastritis
Definition: An American histoplasmosis that results_in inflammation

Name: obsolete Morganella morganii intestinal infectious disease
Definition: An opportunistic bacterial infectious disease that involves infection of the intestine caused by Morganella morganii.

Name: obsolete Vibrio cholerae O139 cholera
Definition: A cholera that involves infection of the intestine caused by Vibrio cholerae O139 strain.

Name: obsolete amebic dysentery
Definition: An amebiasis that involves infection of the intestine with Entamoeba histolytica trophozoites

Name: obsolete Escherichia coli dysentery
Definition: An enteroinvasive Escherichia coli infectious disease that involves infection of the intestine caused by enteroinvasive Escherichia coli. The symptoms include fever

Name: obsolete intestinal capillariasis
Definition: A capillariasis that involves infection of the intestine with Capillaria causing abdominal pain

Name: obsolete hepatic capillariasis
Definition: A capillariasis that involves infection of the liver with Capillaria

Name: obsolete pulmonary capillariasis
Definition: A capillariasis that involves infection of the lungs with Capillaria

Name: obsolete Balamuthia mandrillaris infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by a free-living ameba Balamuthia mandrillaris resulting in encephalitis and skin lesions in humans and animals.

Name: obsolete Acanthamoeba infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves an infection in humans and animals caused by a parasitic protozoan of genus Acanthamoeba

Name: obsolete Alveolata infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by alveolates

Name: obsolete Heterolobosea infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by the members of the class Heterolobosea

Name: obsolete Euglenozoa infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by euglenozoans

Name: obsolete Parabasalia infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by parabasalids

Name: obsolete Fornicata infectious disease
Definition: A parasitic protozoa infectious disease that involves infection caused by fornicates

Name: obsolete Trichomonadida infectious disease
Definition: A Parabasalia infectious disease that involves infection with anaerobic flagellate parasites belonging to the order Trichomonadida. They typically have four to six flagella at the cell's apical pole.

Name: obsolete Tritrichomonadida infectious disease
Definition: A Parabasalia infectious disease that involves infection with anaerobic flagellate parasites belonging to the order Tritrichomonadida

Name: selective IgA deficiency disease
Definition: A selective immunoglobulin deficiency disease that is the result of a deficiency of immunoglobulin A (IgA)

Name: selective IgG deficiency disease
Definition: A dysgammaglobulinemia that is characterized by isolated deficiency of an IgG subclass

Name: selective IgE deficiency disease
Definition: A dysgammaglobulinemia that is characterized by isolated deficiency of IgE and subsequent mildly increased susceptibility to parasitic infections and allergic or autoimmune-related diseases.
